stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Swire 
[Gender] Female 
[Combat Experience] 3 years 
[Place of Birth] Lungmen 
[Date of Birth] Jul. 1 
[Race] Feline 
[Height] 163cm 
[Infection Status] 
Non-infected as confirmed by medical report.

[Physical Strength] Standard 
[Mobility] Standard 
[Physical Resilience] Standard 
[Tactical Acumen] Excellent 
[Combat Skill] Standard 
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Standard

Swire, Senior Superintendent of the Lungmen Guard Department.
Now a special attache at Rhodes Island, providing on-site tactical command.

Imaging tests for this Operator showed clear outlines of internal organs without any unusual dark spots. No abnormal traces of Originium particles present in her system, no symptoms of Oripathy, confirming her as Uninfected. 

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 0% 
No signs of Oripathy present. 

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.13u/L 
Subject's vital indicators are all normal, suggesting she is rarely exposed to Originium. 

Don't worry, Ms. Swire, Rhodes Island's hospital fees are quite reasonable. You only have to pay... 
--S.S.E., Medic Operator 

Any unfair charges to patients will have appropriate consequences. 
-- Dr. Kal'tsit

Swire has no aptitude for manipulating Originium. The most she can do is remote-pilot an Originium drone, but this is adequate for her needs. 
Adding a loudspeaker to such a drone lets her beam her voice to every officer in the field, a technique she has used to great effect! 
But thinking about Swire's voice booming across a battlefield is rather intimidating...

Although her police officers would never say anything in front of Swire, they gossip extensively about her. 
'Swire must be super rich!' 
'Her family business owns some property in Lungmen! And they have even more in Victoria!' 
'Why did she choose to be a police officer instead of inheriting the family business? What was she thinking?' 
The officers would mutter amongst themselves behind Swire's back until they finished their mission or she lashed out at them. They were still fearful of Swire, as she always had her dreaded hammer in hand. 
Now the Rhodes Island Operators do more or less the same thing. 
'She sure is testy. And she's really mean.' -a Lungmen police officer who asked to not be named.

After speaking with Swire, most people find her as passionate as she is strict. 
Swire is fine paying necessary expenses, but if she thinks a bill is too high, becomes intensely suspicious. She will double check her accounts and circle any seemingly dubious charges. 
When she is angry, she deviates from her noble Victorian image. She will charge across the Lungmen street markets and no one can stop her.
Despite this, everyone is still willing to work with her. Swire is not as aggressive as Ch'en, but her focus makes her a good boss. In addition, she is very happy to share when she is in a good mood, and she will often pay everyone who's gone the extra mile out of her own pocket. 
'She really works hard with you. She works like that with everyone.' -a Lungmen police officer who asked to not be named

I still remember that one kidnapping case. 
It must've been before the Guard Department was founded, and Wei Yenwu had decided to clean up Lungmen. This kidnapping was the big thing in that campaign. 
The kidnappers were really something. They had serious firepower, enough to wipe out all our detectives. If we screwed up, they would've killed the hostage and all our effort would've been for nothing. 
The hostage's grandfather was a tough old man who seemed to be Victorian nobility. I think the kidnappers had some reason to go after this kid and it wasn't ransom. They wanted their story to be streamed to the public so Wei Yenwu would look weak. They weren't just ordinary kidnappers. It wasn't that simple. 
The rescue mission was planned by Wei Yenwu and this kid's grandfather. They used a secret special ops team. It's beside the point, but that team was the prototype for the Guard Department's Special Inspection Unit. There were a lot of tabloids and novels written about them. 
Anyway, they pulled it off. The ringleader was executed and most of his accomplices were killed on the spot. 
The hostage? She was just a little girl. The kidnappers clearly didn't think about how traumatic the experience would be for her. 
She didn't end up seeing anything gruesome. She saw a Lungmen police officer rushing out. She saw the heavy Christmas snowfall. She saw the street lamps and the Christmas tree outside the abandoned building. That's pretty good. 
I hope the officers left a good impression on her. 
How do I know all this? Some old police officers told me about it. Everyone's really proud of that mission! 
Hey, don't ask me! I got nothing to hide. 
--A Lungmen Guard Department supervisor

When did she break the habit of stuffing everything in her bag? And when should I forgive her for walking off with my bag, leaving me with nothing but a couple tubes of lipstick and a bottle of foundation to execute an arrest with? 

--An officer who does not want to be named but is named 'Ch'en.'

An outfit commonly worn by Operators.
While not as practical as a uniform, it's what they find most comfortable.

An outfit that has been improved after the Operator's Promotion.
Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.

<color name=#ffffff>0011 New Arrivals/Honor and Splendor. Handcrafted by Lungmen artisans, this outfit synergizes a wide variety of practical fabrics, providing a truly holistic look to meet exacting demands while still maintaining an affordable price.</color>

modules.desc:
Operator Swire has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude in rallying her nearby Melee operators.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Guard Operator during field operations to exercise Instructor responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

Swire, Senior Superintendent of the Lungmen Police Department, is off work today, so, just as always, she goes shopping at Paci Plaza.
After a six-hour shopping spree across the entire mall, she is just getting ready to go home with eight big bags in her hands and a big smile on her face. That is, until she turns the corner to a Swire branded lipstick counter.
'The usual. Five #38 Bullets. Thanks,' Swire masterfully asks the salesperson for her favorite lipstick.
The #38 Bullet has been her lipstick of choice for the past ten years. Naturally, the price is of no concern to her.
'Of course, Miss Swire. Right away,' says the salesperson, who seems to be familiar with this process herself. She asks a coworker to take over at the counter and disappears into the storeroom to look for the lipsticks the princess personally requested. Before long, she returns with a wooden carton and hands it over to Swire.
'Please confirm this is the correct amount.'
Without opening the box to check its contents, Swire merely acknowledges the salesperson and looks down to fish for something in her handbag.
After a good while, she takes out a mini bag. To everyone else, this probably looks more like a petite handbag.
She unbuckles her bag, revealing five black velvet slots inside.
In each of those slots is a used up #38 Bullet lipstick.
Swire removes her used lipsticks and places them on the counter before inserting four of her newly purchased lipsticks in the slots, with the fifth one going into her pocket instead.
When she notices Swire placing her bags back on her shoulders again, the salesperson's heart begins to race.
'Miss, would you like someone to help carry your bags?'
'Oh? No need. They are hardly heavy at all.'
'Frightfully sorry, but are you sure...?'
'Yes, I'm sure,' Swire answers as she walks away from the counter. It seems she really needs no help with her bags.
She may not need any help, but there are others who need hers.
Not a moment after she steps out of the shopping mall's front doors, Swire hears a loud scream for help. She turns to the scream's direction to find a thief dashing away with a woman's handbag in his hands.
It so happens she is running right toward a superintendent of the L.G.D.
'What a coincidence,' Swire thinks to herself.
By chance, she does not have her flail with her.
It so happens she just bought new lipstick today.
What's more, there is one right in her pocket right now.
She decides to teach the thief a lesson he will never forget.
Swire sets her shopping bags down, takes out her lipstick and removes the cap, breaking the seal, and waits for the thief to come closer.
A few seconds later, everyone in the vicinity hears a thud, followed by the thief's wail as he stumbles to the ground under the L.G.D. patrol officer's roar.

Several minutes later...
'Good work, Missy. You're off duty, and you still caught a thief for us.' Hoshiguma, here to oversee the arrest of the thief, forces a smile as she greets Swire, the brave good Samaritan.
Normally, Swire would personally take the man in herself for interrogation.
However, she has the day off. This case isn't hers to deal with.
'This fellow has got to have some real rotten luck to run into me today.'
'It's not every day someone bumps into an off duty inspector when they go to snatch something.'
'Hmph, whatever. You take him in. I'm going home. I'll deal with the case tomorrow.'
'If you say so, Missy.'
'Before you go, I have a question for you.'
'What is it?'
Swire turns around to find Hoshiguma writing something on her case report.
'What should I write for how the suspect was taken down?'
Swire can tell that Hoshiguma is asking for her opinion.
'Just write down that it was lipstick. There is no need to pull punches for someone like him.'
'Ahaha, okay then,' says Hoshiguma as she cheerfully scribbles on her report, 'The suspect was taken down by lipstick.'
'I don't even want to head straight home anymore. Why don't you hurry and finish up with work? We'll get dinner together.'
'Would you like me to escort you home and carry your bags for you, Missy? Haha.'
'Oh, enough questions. Hurry up already.'
'Okay, give me a second. I'll give the report to somebody else, then we can get dinner.'
'Be sure to tell me how amazing this lipstick of yours is.'
'Certainly.'

'Why don't you carry my bags for me now? My hands are getting sore.'
'Okay, okay. Be right with you.

voice_lines.voiceText: Doctor, we can't waste even one single precious minute! One minute could mean a loss of millions on the account with extra casualties on the field! Huh? Coffee? I take it with a sachet of sugar and heavy on the milk foam, thanks!

They say Rhodes Island is a criminal organization, full of Infected people dirtying up the corridors. But that couldn't be further from the truth. Rhodes Island's Operators are giving their lives to make things better for everyone, just like the police force of Lungmen!

Hear me out, do you think we could redesign the instructors' office? At least add a bit of flavor to it, maybe a handmade rug or some atomistic art whatnot. It's just so bland now. Dobermann might say she doesn't care, but it really kills my enthusiasm...

Ahhh, that awful Ch'en isn't here, is she? Back when we were in the L.G.D. together, she shot me this dirty look every time we bumped into each other. It made me wonder if I've done anything bad! I just... kinda want to take over the L.G.D. myself. That couldn't be bad, right?
Exercise, study, training, researching my competitors and market shifts... Gotta keep them up!

I've been allowed to set aside the family business for a while. But it's clear to me that the future of Lungmen needs both a stable public sector and security apparatus, as well as a healthy business and financial system. In both respects, I'm ready to be of service to Lungmen!

Lungmen bureaucracy is complicated, even for us. Keeping the peace, protecting the people, directing traffic, negotiating trade... Agh, it's absolutely backbreaking. But as long as what we do is good for Lungmen, I'll be—hehe—very pleased.

Doctor, why is Rhodes Island's training course so short...? Insufficient capital? Unacceptable, I'm requesting an immediate transfer to the business division! It's-it's not as if I like business, but if you need me to do it, I'm... more than capable!

You know, Doctor, Lungmen could use someone as talented as you. So, well... If you're not enjoying this line of work, there's plenty of opportunities in the banking and management sectors! I-I can get you a job! Oh? You'd rather we work with Rhodes Island? ...Fine!
Uughh... I'm exhausted... Two shifts in a row really does... zzz... zzz...
Swire, Senior Superintendent of the L.G.D.. I'll be joining Rhodes Island as a training consultant. Dr. {@nickname}, I'm looking forward to working together with you for the future of Lungmen!
Hmm, as far as tactical theory goes, this is a decent application!
A promotion? Hmm? But it doesn't do anything for me back in Lungmen, does it? Well, if you insist, I suppose I will accept it!

Maybe it's that you want me to improve your relationship with Lungmen. Or, possibly, you truly need my talents. I suppose it could be something else you want, too... I'm not sure exactly what, and I can't promise it'll be on offer. But I'll be a stalwart with you to the end.
Aha~! You finally need my wisdom!
Everyone, follow my orders to the letter!
Wipe them out in one fell swoop! It's cheaper that way!
Let's finish this quickly. My time is far too precious!
Huh?
I've seen through the enemy's strategies!
This is far from my only battlefield!
Business competitor or not, you will get a lesson from me!
Time is money!
Hurry it up, let's move!
Lungmen has its own pride!
Time to liquidate!
Fantastic! In battle as in business: high risk, high return!
Capital is all mergers and acquisitions! Victory is like investigation and arrest!
...Bad... just bad... You can do better, can't you? We'll work it out together. Don't give up!
How could this have happened? How could I... How could I have blundered so badly?!
Not bad... No, I think this room could use some more renovation!
Ah! How rude of you!
How... How about we go for dinner together? M-my treat!
Arknights.

Happy New Year! Look at this crowd! So many people here! I brought some Lungmen street food with me... I-I didn't bring it for you guys! I wanted to have some myself! Right, if Ch'en has any, make sure she pays for her share. Call it a handling fee.
Doctor, roar!

Look at you always wearing that outfit. You gotta at least change your shoes sometimes. Here, look what I've brought for you. Dark, flat, no design sensibility whatsoever. The brand I usually wear just got a bunch of new styles, and I picked out a few pairs for you based on your tastes. But looking like that, nobody will be able to tell they're luxury branded! What a waste!

I went against my grandfather's wishes by becoming a cop, but I believe it was the right choice for me, not that it's easy. This isn't just to take control of my own life. More than that, it's for Lungmen's future. Hey, don't think Ch'en's the only one who thinks about this stuff. Just like her, I have much to do in the future.
